---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'
import BoneTexture from '../assets/images/frame-bio_bone-texture.svg'
import CollagenTexture from '../assets/images/frame-bio_collagen-texture.svg'
import FrameBioFigureTwo from '../assets/images/frame-bio_figure-2.svg'
import FrameBioFigure from '../assets/images/frame-bio_figure-leaning-stretch.svg'
import PillsTexture from '../assets/images/frame-bio_pills-texture.svg'
import FrameBioPipelineGrid from '../assets/images/frame-bio_pipeline-grid-section.svg'
import SkinBoneAxisLockup from '../assets/images/frame-bio_skin-bone-axis-lockup.svg'
import FrameBioVerticalPipeline from '../assets/images/frame-bio_vertical-pipeline-grid.svg'
import highResImage from '../assets/images/high-res-exosome-image.png'
import Contact from '../components/forms/Contact.astro'
import Header from '../components/ui/Header.astro'
import ProductCard from '../components/ui/ProductCard.astro'
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout>
  <Header />
  <main class="pb-0">
    <section id="about" class="md:pt-0">
      <h2 class="sr-only">About Frame Bio</h2>
      <div class="wrapper">
        <div
          id="targeted-therapies-grid"
          class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-(--site-padding-base) gap-y-(--site-padding-lg)"
        >
          <FrameBioFigure
            class="hidden md:block h-auto max-w-lg mr-auto lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat"
          />
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-(--site-padding-base) w-full lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat">
            <h3 class="text-[clamp(1rem,7.25vw,2.25rem)]">Targeted therapies for the</h3>
            <SkinBoneAxisLockup class="max-w-md" />
            <h4 class="text-3xl text-secondary mt-8">
              A Novel Paradigm for Relieving Structural Diseases &amp; Disorders
            </h4>
            <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-sm)">
              <p>
                With almost a third of the global population affected by skin diseases and more than
                200 million people worldwide suffering from osteoporosis, there is significant need
                for therapies targeting skin and bone issues. At Frame Bio, we're developing better
                methods for delivering such therapies directly to bones, joints, tendons, and
                collagen to enhance the body's natural repair processes.
              </p>
              <p>
                Emerging research suggests that our skin and bones may be more connected than we
                thought. Through hormones, vitamins, and the immune system, it appears that these
                two systems talk to each other; when one is struggling, the other often does too.
                This crosstalk, known as the skin-bone axis, is seen in the relationship between
                skin diseases and bone disease, and serves as inspiration for Frame Bio's research.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Treatment Tags - Second Row, Spanning Both Columns -->
          <div
            class="md:col-span-2 grid grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4 gap-4 lsa lsa-slide-up no-repeat"
          >
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 flex-shrink-0 bg-secondary rounded-full animate-pulse"></div>
              <p class="h5 font-museo-slab-rounded">Bone</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 flex-shrink-0 bg-secondary rounded-full animate-pulse"></div>
              <p class="h5 font-museo-slab-rounded">Collagen</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 flex-shrink-0 bg-secondary rounded-full animate-pulse"></div>
              <p class="h5 font-museo-slab-rounded">Tendons/Joints</p>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <div class="w-3 h-3 flex-shrink-0 bg-secondary rounded-full animate-pulse"></div>
              <p class="h5 font-museo-slab-rounded">Cartilage</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <FrameBioFigure
            class="block md:hidden h-auto max-w-lg mr-auto lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="our-tech">
      <div class="wrapper">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-(--site-padding-xl) justify-items-center items-center">
          <!-- Left Column: Text Content -->
          <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-base) lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat">
            <h2 class="text-secondary font-museo-slab-rounded uppercase">CORE TECHNOLOGY</h2>
            <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-sm)">
              <p>
                One of the best ways to improve the success of a drug in development is to ensure
                that it reaches the areas of the body that need it most. Not only can this improve
                the overall efficacy of the drug, it may also reduce the negative side effects that
                can often accompany off-target delivery. When therapeutics are directed to where
                they're needed most—versus being diluted across unrelated organs and bodily
                systems—their potency is naturally increased.
              </p>
              <p>
                At Frame Bio, we've employed a novel method of extracellular vesicle (EV) drug
                encapsulation developed by <a
                  href="https://www.mercurybio.com/"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="link">Mercury Bio Inc.</a
                > to deliver therapies directly to injured bone, joints, and other tissues. Mercury Bio's
                yEV™ technology works with the body's natural transport system, precisely targeting
                cells and depositing molecular therapies directly to them.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Right Column: Exosome Image with Static Annotations -->
          <figure class="max-w-[500px] space-y-(--site-padding-sm) lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat">
            <Image
              src={highResImage}
              alt="High resolution exosome structure"
              class="drop-shadow-2xl"
              width={highResImage.width}
              height={highResImage.height}
            />

            <figcaption class="ml-auto w-1/2">
              <p class="caption">
                An extracellular vesicle is a nanoscale, membrane-bound particle (about 30-1000
                nanometers in diameter) that cells naturally release for intercellular
                communication. They carry proteins, lipids, and nucleic acids to transmit signals
                and regulate the behavior of other cells.
              </p>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="products" class="overflow-x-hidden">
      <div class="wrapper">
        <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-base)">
          <h2 class="text-secondary font-museo-slab-rounded uppercase lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat">
            Product Development
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-(--site-padding-lg) lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat">
            Currently, Frame Bio is researching three unique product lines, each addressing
            different components of the skin-bone axis. We aim to improve quality of life for
            millions of people suffering from inflammation and discomfort tied to bone disease and
            connective tissue disorders.
          </p>

          <!-- Product Cards -->
          <div class="h-full flex flex-col gap-(--site-padding-lg)">
            <ProductCard
              title="Collagen Regeneration"
              description={[
                'Collagen is a fiber-like structural protein found in tendons, ligaments, joints, and bones. Many collagen diseases are autoimmune, resulting from an overactive immune system that mistakenly attacks healthy collagen. Existing treatments for collagen disorders often focus on reducing inflammation and improving mobility. This can be accomplished with medication, surgery, dietary supplements, or a combination of these.',
                "Frame Bio's research aims to develop targeted collagen therapies that augment natural regenerative processes, meaning fewer surgical interventions and less need for medications that affect the entire body. By delivering signaling proteins to the source of skin and bone disease, Frame Bio's novel therapeutics look beyond mere symptom relief in favor of returning tissues to fundamentally healthier states.",
              ]}
              image={CollagenTexture}
              imageAlt="Illustration of collagen regeneration"
              numeral={1}
            />

            <ProductCard
              title="Bone Regeneration via BMP-2"
              description={[
                'Bones are in a constant state of growth and deterioration. When the balance between these processes is disrupted, it affects bone density. Historically, treatment of low bone density has included dietary supplements and medications called bisphosphonates, but these can bring unwanted side effects, and long-term use has few benefits. Recent research has explored the use of a naturally produced protein called BMP, or bone morphogenetic protein. BMP-2 is currently approved by the FDA to heal fractures in certain bones and for use in spinal fusion surgery. While various forms of BMP have proven effective in bone remodeling, better delivery methods are needed to control the timing and location of release within the body.',
                "Frame Bio's solution utilizes hydroxyapatite, a form of calcium found naturally in bones and teeth. This compound can improve the binding of BMP-2 to bone tissues, thereby delivering it directly to damaged bone. Through a research partnership with Himed—one of the world's leading producers of hydroxyapatite technologies for orthopedic devices—we’ve identified a means of deploying BMP-2 in bone scaffolding materials that are commonly used to repair hard-tissue breaks and fractures. We're future-proofing this application method by exploring how it translates into the new world of patient-specific 3D-printed implants. As healthcare becomes even more personalized and customized, our technology will be ready.",
              ]}
              image={BoneTexture}
              imageAlt="Illustration of bone regeneration"
              numeral={2}
            />

            <ProductCard
              title="Nutraceutical Development"
              description={[
                'A nutraceutical is a food-derived product—ranging from isolated nutrients to herbal extracts—used for health benefits beyond basic nutrition. In the context of bone and joint health, widely studied examples include calcium and vitamin D for maintaining bone density; collagen peptides, glucosamine, and chondroitin for supporting cartilage and joint strength; omega-3 fatty acids and curcumin for their anti-inflammatory properties; and isoflavones or hyaluronic acid for reinforcing bone strength and joint lubrication.',
                "Even when these compounds have plausible biological roles, their benefits are often limited by poor bioavailability and off-target delivery, leaving only small amounts to reach bone or cartilage in effective concentrations. The use of a targeted drug delivery system addresses these challenges, opening the door to maximizing nutraceutical efficacy. Frame Bio's initial focus is on natural compounds with strong anti-inflammatory activity that may help reduce use of NSAID painkillers for connective tissue pain.",
              ]}
              image={PillsTexture}
              imageAlt="Illustration of pill regeneration"
              numeral={3}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section
      id="pipeline"
      class="bg-primary text-primary-content overflow-x-hidden mb-(--site-padding-2xl)"
    >
      <div class="wrapper xl:pt-100">
        <!-- Header with Title and Figure -->
        <div
          class="relative grid xl:grid-cols-2 items-end gap-(--site-padding-base) mb-(--site-padding-2xl)"
        >
          <div class="xl:order-2 lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat xl:absolute xl:-right-100 w-full">
            <Image
              src={FrameBioFigureTwo}
              alt="Illustration of person in a crow pose yoga position"
              class="h-auto mx-auto block w-full max-w-xl"
            />
          </div>
          <h2
            class="text-secondary text-center xl:text-nowrap font-museo-slab-rounded uppercase lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat"
          >
            Drug Development Pipeline
          </h2>
        </div>

        <!-- Pipeline Charts -->

        <!-- Mobile -->
        <div
          class="relative mx-auto flex flex-col items-center xl:hidden gap-(--site-padding-lg) lsa lsa-slide-up no-repeat h-full max-w-2xl"
        >
          <!-- Column Headers -->
          <div
            class="w-full grid grid-cols-[1fr_4fr_4fr] gap-(--site-padding-base) mb-(--site-padding-base)"
          >
            <!-- Empty space for row labels -->
            <div class="w-full"></div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-secondary uppercase">BMP-2</h4>
              <p class="leading-tight">
                <span class="uppercase"
                  >Bone Morphogenic<br />
                  Protein</span
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="text-secondary uppercase">Collagen 1</h4>
              <p class="leading-tight">
                <span class="uppercase"
                  >Collagen Protein<br />
                  Regeneration</span
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Pipeline Grid Container -->
          <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-[1fr_4fr_4fr] gap-(--site-padding-base) relative">
            <!-- Left Column: Row Labels -->
            <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-around h-full">
              <h4 class="[writing-mode:vertical-rl] text-accent uppercase">Discovery</h4>
              <h4 class="[writing-mode:vertical-rl] text-accent uppercase">Pre-Clinical</h4>
              <h4 class="[writing-mode:vertical-rl] text-accent uppercase">IND-Enabling</h4>
            </div>

            <!-- Pipeline Grid Background -->
            <div class="col-span-2 relative">
              <Image
                src={FrameBioVerticalPipeline}
                alt="Pipeline Grid"
                class="opacity-10 w-full h-full object-cover"
              />

              <!-- BMP-2 Progress Bar -->
              <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/4 h-1/3 flex justify-center items-start">
                <div class="relative h-full w-6 flex justify-center">
                  <!-- Circle -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute top-0 w-5 h-5 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full z-1"
                  >
                  </div>
                  <!-- Line -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute top-2.5 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 h-[150%] w-1 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Collagen Progress Bar -->
              <div class="absolute top-0 right-1/4 h-1/3 flex justify-center items-start">
                <div class="relative h-full w-6 flex justify-center">
                  <!-- Circle -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute top-0 w-5 h-5 bg-white rounded-full z-1 shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)]"
                  >
                  </div>
                  <!-- Line -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute top-2.5 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 h-[80%] w-1 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Caption -->
          <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-base) mt-(--site-padding-lg)">
            <p>
              Frame Bio has two therapies already under development: one that targets bone
              regeneration and another that aims to strengthen connective tissues by catalyzing
              collagen production. Both product lines harness the intercellular communications that
              occur with extracellular vesicles to deliver therapeutics that trigger the body's
              natural healing processes.
            </p>

            <!-- Bottom Icon/Text for Mobile -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-accent">
              <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                height="24px"
                width="24px"
                viewBox="0 -960 960 960"
                fill="currentColor"
                class="size-6 flex-shrink-0"
                ><path
                  d="M401 0q-83 0-156-31.5t-127.5-86Q63-172 31.5-245T0-400q0-83 31.5-156t86-127.5Q172-738 245-769.5T401-801q10 0 19.5.5T440-799v80q-10-1-19.5-1.5T401-721q-134 0-227.5 93.5T80-400q0 133 93.5 226.5T401-80q133 0 226.5-93.5T721-400h80q0 82-31.5 155t-86 127.5q-54.5 54.5-127 86T401 0Zm131-212L360-384v-216h80v184l148 148-56 56Zm342-268q-23-142-120-246.5T520-866v-82q171 37 290.5 165T955-480h-81Zm-163 0q-19-75-69.5-132T520-698v-85q103 32 177 113.5T793-480h-82Z"
                ></path></svg
              >
              <p class="caption">
                Want to stay connected to Frame Bio's product development process? <a
                  href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/frame-bio/"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener"
                  class="link caption">Follow our company on LinkedIn</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Desktop -->
        <div class="hidden xl:block space-y-(--site-padding-lg) lsa lsa-slide-up no-repeat">
          <!-- Column Headers -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-(--site-padding-base) mb-(--site-padding-base)">
            <div></div>
            <!-- Empty space for row labels -->
            <div class="text-center">
              <h4 class="text-accent uppercase text-xl">Discovery</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <h4 class="text-accent uppercase text-xl">Pre-Clinical</h4>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center">
              <h4 class="text-accent uppercase text-xl">IND-Enabling</h4>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-(--site-padding-base) items-center mb-(--site-padding-lg)"
          >
            <!-- Row Labels -->
            <div class="space-y-8">
              <div class="space-y-2">
                <h4 class="text-xl font-museo-slab-rounded font-bold uppercase text-secondary">
                  BMP-2
                </h4>
                <p class="leading-tight">
                  <span class="uppercase"
                    >Bone Morphogenic<br />
                    Protein</span
                  >
                </p>
              </div>
              <!-- Row Label -->
              <div class="space-y-2">
                <h4 class="font-museo-slab-rounded font-bold uppercase text-secondary text-xl">
                  Collagen 1
                </h4>
                <p class="leading-tight">
                  <span class="uppercase"
                    >Collagen Protein<br />
                    Regeneration</span
                  >
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Grid Background (3 sections) -->
            <div class="col-span-3 relative">
              <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
                <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
                <Image src={FrameBioPipelineGrid} alt="Pipeline Grid" class="opacity-30" />
              </div>

              <!-- 1st Progress Bar Overlay -->
              <div class="absolute top-12 left-0 w-1/2 flex items-center">
                <div class="relative w-full h-6 flex items-center">
                  <!-- Circle -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full z-1"
                  >
                  </div>
                  <!-- Line -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute left-2.5 h-1 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full"
                    style="width: 100%;"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- 2nd Progress Bar Overlay -->
              <div class="absolute bottom-12 left-0 w-1/4 flex items-center">
                <div class="relative w-full h-6 flex items-center">
                  <!-- Circle -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute left-0 w-5 h-5 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full z-1"
                  >
                  </div>
                  <!-- Line -->
                  <div
                    class="absolute left-2.5 h-1 bg-white shadow-[0_0_0_6px_var(--color-base-200)] rounded-full"
                    style="width: 100%;"
                  >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Footer Text -->
          <div class="flex justify-between gap-8">
            <p class="max-w-2xl">
              Frame Bio has two therapies already under development: one which targets bone
              regeneration, and another that aims to strengthen connective tissues by catalyzing
              collagen production. Both product lines harness the intercellular communications that
              occur with extra cellular vesicles to deliver therapeutics which trigger the body's
              natural healing processes.
            </p>

            <!-- Caption -->

            <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-accent">
              <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                height="24px"
                width="24px"
                viewBox="0 -960 960 960"
                fill="currentColor"
                class="size-8"
                ><path
                  d="M401 0q-83 0-156-31.5t-127.5-86Q63-172 31.5-245T0-400q0-83 31.5-156t86-127.5Q172-738 245-769.5T401-801q10 0 19.5.5T440-799v80q-10-1-19.5-1.5T401-721q-134 0-227.5 93.5T80-400q0 133 93.5 226.5T401-80q133 0 226.5-93.5T721-400h80q0 82-31.5 155t-86 127.5q-54.5 54.5-127 86T401 0Zm131-212L360-384v-216h80v184l148 148-56 56Zm342-268q-23-142-120-246.5T520-866v-82q171 37 290.5 165T955-480h-81Zm-163 0q-19-75-69.5-132T520-698v-85q103 32 177 113.5T793-480h-82Z"
                ></path></svg
              >
              <p class="caption">
                Want to stay connected to Frame Bio's product development process? <a
                  href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/frame-bio/"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener"
                  class="link caption">Follow our company on LinkedIn</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="relative">
      <!-- Pulse Effect -->
      <div
        class="left-0 top-0 absolute w-full h-full md:w-[calc(100%-var(--site-padding-4xl))] xl:w-[calc(100%-var(--site-padding-5xl))] shadow-[0_0_20px] shadow-secondary z-0 animate-pulse"
      >
      </div>
      <!-- Background -->
      <div
        id="contact-bg"
        class="left-0 top-0 absolute w-full h-full md:w-[calc(100%-var(--site-padding-4xl))] xl:w-[calc(100%-var(--site-padding-5xl))] bg-primary z-2"
      >
      </div>
      <div class="wrapper relative z-2">
        <div class="space-y-(--site-padding-base) md:pr-(--site-padding-md)">
          <h2 class="text-secondary font-museo-slab-rounded uppercase lsa lsa-slide-left no-repeat">
            Contact Frame Bio
          </h2>
          <p class="lsa lsa-slide-right no-repeat">
            <strong>Want to help advance a new paradigm for bone and joint health?</strong> We're building
            next-generation therapies that go beyond managing symptoms—aiming to repair, restore, and
            truly change the trajectory of skeletal and connective tissue disorders. If you're developing
            novel therapeutics for skin and bone disorders, or investing in breakthrough ideas, we want
            to connect with you.
          </p>

          <Contact />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
